WEBVTT

01:54.250 --> 01:56.250
<i>The police investigation continues</i>

01:56.250 --> 01:58.708
<i>at Trent Hamilton Agricultural College
in Shropshire,</i>

01:58.708 --> 02:02.500
<i>after one of its students was arrested
for membership of the IRA.</i>

02:02.500 --> 02:07.583
<i>The authorities are concerned
that Kevin Barry, 22, from County Tyrone,</i>

02:07.583 --> 02:11.208
<i>may have been part of a wider IRA cell
operating in the area.</i>

02:24.833 --> 02:26.250
Just drive on through, sir.

03:04.125 --> 03:06.083
<i>There's a trick that spies use.</i>

03:07.250 --> 03:09.916
<i>He told me they learn it
on their first day of training.</i>

03:13.333 --> 03:16.166
<i>If you want to make
an instant connection with someone,</i>

03:16.666 --> 03:18.083
<i>look into their eyes,</i>

03:19.041 --> 03:21.666
<i>just long enough
to register their eye color.</i>

03:23.583 --> 03:25.125
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:27.416 --> 03:29.416
Uh... I'm here about the job.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.041
- Yeah. Come in.
- Thanks.

03:32.125 --> 03:34.125
<i>He said it works every time.</i>

03:43.416 --> 03:45.666
<i>He learned how to hide in plain sight.</i>

03:53.708 --> 03:55.125
<i>How to read people.</i>

03:59.583 --> 04:01.125
-

04:01.125 --> 04:02.125
Thank you!

04:02.125 --> 04:03.458
Thank you so much!

04:05.833 --> 04:08.041
Are you sure I can't buy you a drink?

04:08.708 --> 04:09.958
I don't drink.

04:10.416 --> 04:11.458
Uh...

04:14.541 --> 04:17.333
<i>He learned how to recruit
the right people.</i>

04:19.625 --> 04:20.791
Listen, Ian.

04:21.958 --> 04:24.708
There is something
I've been meaning to talk to you about.

04:25.208 --> 04:26.291
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

04:26.375 --> 04:27.625
You and your friends.

04:27.625 --> 04:28.750
Uh...

04:28.750 --> 04:30.083
Not here, though.

04:30.625 --> 04:32.166
<i>How to persuade them.</i>

04:33.250 --> 04:34.375
You're a spy?

04:35.541 --> 04:38.375
I... I'm an officer
in the British security services.

04:40.041 --> 04:44.083
The IRA cell have been installed
here at Trent Hamilton for over a year.

04:45.000 --> 04:46.750
They are posing as students.

04:47.416 --> 04:49.375
Stealing fertilizer to create bombs.

04:51.333 --> 04:52.666
As you know,

04:53.500 --> 04:55.375
one of them was recently caught
back in Ireland,

04:55.375 --> 04:57.208
trying to blow up a police station.

04:58.166 --> 05:00.875
And the others are still here,
on active service.

05:02.750 --> 05:03.625
Bloody hell.

05:03.625 --> 05:05.541
Can't believe this is happening.

05:08.125 --> 05:09.166
Sorry.

05:09.666 --> 05:10.916
What can we do about it?

05:12.041 --> 05:12.916
Plenty.

05:13.416 --> 05:15.416
Get close to them in ways that I can't.

05:15.500 --> 05:17.958
Find out things
that could really help our investigation.

05:17.958 --> 05:19.041
No.

05:20.291 --> 05:21.791
I'm sorry, no.

05:22.708 --> 05:23.708
Sophie.

05:25.250 --> 05:26.250
Sit down.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.000
Sit.

05:42.791 --> 05:44.750
If you help me do my job,

05:44.750 --> 05:46.875
it will save lives.

05:48.958 --> 05:50.375
I promise you that.

05:54.000 --> 05:55.000
Men.

05:56.541 --> 05:57.541
Women.

06:00.333 --> 06:01.333
Children.

06:06.875 --> 06:08.500
Just read...

06:09.375 --> 06:10.583
- Hey.
- Hey.

06:10.583 --> 06:11.833
- Hey.
- How you doing?

06:11.833 --> 06:13.333
- Grand. You?
- Good.

06:13.333 --> 06:16.458
<i>He said
that espionage is storytelling.</i>

06:16.458 --> 06:17.833
<i>Sláinte!</i>

06:17.833 --> 06:20.875
<i>And everyone has a story
they want to be told.</i>

06:20.875 --> 06:22.041
Never heard of it.

06:22.125 --> 06:23.541
Tonight is the night.

06:26.041 --> 06:28.291
Tonight, we put into practice
everything I have taught you.

06:28.375 --> 06:29.458
over the last three months.

06:30.666 --> 06:32.625
And remember, this is not a test.

06:33.500 --> 06:35.208
There is no room for failure.

06:36.333 --> 06:37.333
Okay?

06:39.125 --> 06:40.291
Sophie, Mae.

06:42.250 --> 06:43.458
What's your role?

06:44.541 --> 06:45.666
To clear the house.

06:46.250 --> 06:47.416
Get everyone out.

06:49.125 --> 06:51.541
<i>- But there's a moment you have to act.</i>
- Well, listen!

06:51.625 --> 06:54.958
<i>- And that is the moment of maximum risk.</i>
- On that note, I have an announcement.

06:54.958 --> 06:58.833
So I think we should all go
across the road to the Swan,

06:58.833 --> 07:00.791
where I'll buy everyone a round.

07:00.875 --> 07:02.208
- Yes!
-

07:02.208 --> 07:04.208
And that's an offer
we can't refuse. Let's go!

07:04.208 --> 07:05.541
Let's go!

07:05.625 --> 07:06.666
Come on!

07:06.750 --> 07:10.291
<i>In that world, duplicity is a necessity.</i>

07:11.458 --> 07:13.083
Niall, I'm gonna use your toilet.

07:13.083 --> 07:15.041
- Go in the pub.
- Mate, I'm bursting.

07:15.125 --> 07:17.916
- I'll follow you over in a sec.
- Fine. It's upstairs.

07:18.708 --> 07:20.208
- Cool. Ready?
- We ready?

07:20.208 --> 07:21.583
- Let's go, guys!
- Let's go.

07:31.375 --> 07:33.666
- I left my jacket here.
- You're paranoid.

07:33.750 --> 07:35.291
I don't like that, there's no surprise.

07:35.375 --> 07:37.125
- Then I can surprise you.
- Surprise me!

07:37.125 --> 07:38.583
- Nah, I'm not doing that.
- Oh, yeah!

07:38.583 --> 07:40.708
-
- Can you get me a pint of water?

07:43.583 --> 07:46.666
<i>But the greater the ruse,
the bigger the risk.</i>

07:48.750 --> 07:51.208
Oh shit. I forgot my wallet.

07:51.208 --> 07:53.666
- Doesn't matter. I'm buying.
- I'll just be a minute.

07:53.750 --> 07:56.166
- You can just get it later.
- It's fine, honestly.

07:56.250 --> 07:57.250
Oh, come on.

07:57.250 --> 07:58.250
See you.

08:55.875 --> 08:57.375
You didn't take a shit, did you?

09:04.875 --> 09:06.375
Yeah, there was nothing there.

09:19.208 --> 09:20.208
Thank you.

09:20.875 --> 09:22.375
- Cheers, everyone.
- Cheers.

09:22.375 --> 09:25.958
<i>His world was thrilling and mysterious.</i>

09:28.666 --> 09:30.375
<i>But it came at a cost.</i>

09:32.666 --> 09:33.625
Sophie.

09:34.416 --> 09:35.333
Sophie.

09:35.833 --> 09:37.666
Sophie, get up. Get up!

09:37.750 --> 09:39.166
- What?
- We've been compromised.

09:39.250 --> 09:41.833
We're extracting. You need to get up.

09:41.833 --> 09:43.625
- What?
- They know about us.

09:44.125 --> 09:45.833
About you. Okay? They know.

09:46.875 --> 09:47.833
Sophie---No!

09:47.833 --> 09:49.333
You do not have a choice.

09:49.333 --> 09:51.791
They could be here any second.
Get up. Come on.

09:54.541 --> 09:56.541
-

09:59.375 --> 10:00.750
<i>A cost to him...</i>

10:02.125 --> 10:03.458
<i>and to others.</i>

10:05.958 --> 10:07.708
- What happens now?
- I don't know.

10:07.708 --> 10:09.500
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

10:09.500 --> 10:11.416
I never had an agent compromised before.

10:12.166 --> 10:14.291
But I promise you, I will protect you.

10:19.458 --> 10:20.875
I will keep you safe.

10:37.583 --> 10:41.416
<i>Anyone who entered that world
left behind the lives they had before.</i>

10:44.083 --> 10:45.708
<i>People they once were.</i>

10:46.833 --> 10:48.916
<i>That was the price they had to pay.</i>

11:12.708 --> 11:13.833
So you have it?

11:15.375 --> 11:16.625
And what does it say?

11:20.083 --> 11:21.125
Perfect.

11:22.416 --> 11:23.875
Oh, yeah. Usual place.

11:25.791 --> 11:27.416
No, she's a beautiful car.

11:28.000 --> 11:30.875
Beautiful. She won't let you down.
She's simple, elegant.

11:31.458 --> 11:33.125
- You've made the right decision.
- Mmm.

11:40.333 --> 11:42.500
Believe me.
It's a whole new world.

11:50.041 --> 11:51.041
Thank you.

11:55.083 --> 11:56.583
So, Andrew, where is she?

11:57.166 --> 11:58.583
You know what the trains are like.

11:58.583 --> 12:00.416
- Come on.
- She travels by train?

12:03.458 --> 12:05.250
Alice, welcome.

12:05.750 --> 12:07.416
Nice of you to join us.

12:12.500 --> 12:14.041
There's been a development.

12:15.083 --> 12:17.916
An email chain
between senior managers at the bank

12:18.833 --> 12:21.041
proving they did indeed
verbally agree with you

12:21.125 --> 12:23.166
to waive the security over the assets.

12:23.833 --> 12:26.583
An agreement
that they not only failed to disclose,

12:26.583 --> 12:29.958
but it now seems,
have actively tried to cover up,

12:30.791 --> 12:33.333
which is potentially criminal
on their part.

12:34.041 --> 12:36.416
Certainly, it blows their case
out of the water.

12:37.458 --> 12:39.125
- How did we...
-

12:42.666 --> 12:43.916
Aaah!

12:44.416 --> 12:46.708
I rather feel a celebration is in order.

12:56.083 --> 12:58.833
I must say, Alice, I'm most impressed.

12:58.833 --> 12:59.916
Thank you.

13:01.208 --> 13:03.333
And you're also not a bad lawyer.

13:05.500 --> 13:08.416
-
- I'm joking! I'm joking!

13:10.041 --> 13:11.166
Sam! More drinks.

13:11.750 --> 13:14.000
- Another bottle of Bollinger.
- Are you okay?

13:21.166 --> 13:22.208
Hi there.

13:23.708 --> 13:25.750
I saw you walking past this morning.

13:27.000 --> 13:28.791
In fact, I see you most mornings.

13:28.875 --> 13:29.750
Oh, fuck off, mate.

13:48.750 --> 13:50.083
-

13:50.083 --> 13:51.250
-

14:04.958 --> 14:07.541
Oh God.

14:44.625 --> 14:45.500
Hi.

14:47.625 --> 14:49.166
- Hi.
- Look.

14:49.916 --> 14:53.416
I wanted to apologize for last night.

14:54.125 --> 14:57.041
- I was rude.
- No, no, it was, uh... it was my fault.

14:57.625 --> 15:01.708
You must get completely fed up with men
coming up and talking to you all the time.

15:02.583 --> 15:04.500
I apologize. It won't happen again.

15:06.166 --> 15:07.166
Okay.

15:08.083 --> 15:09.083
Well,

15:10.333 --> 15:11.333
good.

15:14.916 --> 15:17.625
On a scale of one to ten,
how hungover are you?

15:20.000 --> 15:20.833
Fourteen.

15:22.125 --> 15:25.000
And you're gonna get the Tube
on a hot summer's day like today?

15:26.333 --> 15:28.916
- Hey, I'll give you a lift.
- What?

15:29.500 --> 15:31.208
I'll tell the manager
you want a test drive.

15:31.208 --> 15:34.041
No, no, I-- I really don't think that--

15:34.125 --> 15:35.458
I'll put the roof down.

15:35.458 --> 15:38.041
If you wanna puke,
you can just do it over the side.

15:38.541 --> 15:40.583
- Preferably on a cyclist.
-

15:42.583 --> 15:43.541
Take the BMW.

15:45.708 --> 15:48.666
<i>♪ Beetles and eggs and blues ♪</i>

15:48.750 --> 15:52.875
<i>♪ And pour a little everythin' else ♪</i>

15:54.833 --> 15:58.000
<i>♪ As good news ♪</i>

15:58.000 --> 16:04.041
<i>♪ Still we can find our love
Down from behind ♪</i>

16:08.708 --> 16:15.041
<i>♪ Down from behind this fabulous
My turn rules ♪</i>

16:17.000 --> 16:18.083
Thanks.

16:29.375 --> 16:30.375
My card.

16:31.625 --> 16:33.625
In case you wanna buy a car.

16:34.125 --> 16:35.125
Or have dinner.

16:36.291 --> 16:37.541
Robert Hansen.

16:39.458 --> 16:40.416
Look, um...

16:41.416 --> 16:45.416
I'm not trying to be an arsehole here,
but I should put my cards on the table.

16:46.166 --> 16:47.708
I, uh... I don't usually--

16:47.708 --> 16:50.500
You don't usually date guys
who sell cars for a living.

16:52.375 --> 16:54.916
Have you had bad experiences
with car salesmen before?

17:00.416 --> 17:01.708
Okay.

17:02.708 --> 17:04.541
Well, top marks for persistence.

17:05.666 --> 17:07.041
Tomorrow night works for me.

17:08.250 --> 17:11.416
- Pick you up at eight?
- You don't know where I live.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.583
A couple of doors down from the showroom.

17:15.166 --> 17:17.041
You own a blue Mercedes.

17:17.875 --> 17:19.375
It's not a bad car, that.

17:25.375 --> 17:26.791
See you, tomorrow, Alice.

17:38.041 --> 17:40.791
<i>♪ At least you know
But either way ♪</i>

17:40.875 --> 17:45.458
<i>♪ I wanna call but you're so far away... ♪</i>

17:50.000 --> 17:53.083
<i>♪ Come on and say, somebody said ♪</i>

17:53.083 --> 17:56.875
<i>♪ You're not helping
You're so far away... ♪</i>

18:21.625 --> 18:22.916
Prick.

18:23.000 --> 18:25.083
It's really a question
of loan-to-value ratio

18:25.083 --> 18:27.791
and whether we can roll
the wider assets into the case.

18:27.875 --> 18:31.333
In my view, because the holding company
is named in the contract, we can.

18:31.333 --> 18:33.916
If anybody disagrees, I'm all ears.

18:36.250 --> 18:37.125
Alice?

18:38.541 --> 18:40.083
-
- We good?

18:40.708 --> 18:41.583
Yeah.

18:42.916 --> 18:44.750
All right. You know what to do.

18:58.291 --> 18:59.708
Don't think so, mate.

18:59.708 --> 19:00.958
Fuckin' idiot.

19:14.166 --> 19:16.708
- Yeah?
- <i>I'm so sorry about last night.</i>

19:16.708 --> 19:19.250
Okay, well, you don't get
a second chance, I'm afraid.

19:19.250 --> 19:22.208
- Don't contact me again. <i>- My dad was taken to hospital.</i>

19:23.041 --> 19:24.083
Your dad?

19:24.083 --> 19:25.458
<i>That's why I couldn't call.</i>

19:25.458 --> 19:28.041
<i>I was by his bedside all night.
They don't allow phones.</i>

19:28.125 --> 19:30.291
<i>I'm-- I'm so sorry, I really am.</i>

19:30.916 --> 19:32.166
Is he okay?

19:33.000 --> 19:34.125
<i>Uh...</i>

19:34.125 --> 19:36.333
<i>Yeah, yeah, I think so.</i>

19:36.333 --> 19:39.000
<i>Uh, it was a bit of difficult evening,
to be honest.</i>

19:40.083 --> 19:41.000
Oh.

19:42.125 --> 19:43.125
Okay.

19:44.250 --> 19:46.750
<i>Listen, I'm, uh... I'm outside.</i>

19:47.791 --> 19:49.083
You're outside?

19:49.750 --> 19:50.875
<i>Yeah, yeah</i>

19:52.458 --> 19:53.708
Can I come in?

19:53.708 --> 19:56.333
No, you can't come in.
I don't even know you.

19:57.875 --> 20:00.250
Oh, yeah. Um... Of course. Well...

20:01.083 --> 20:03.708
<i>Well, look, can I leave this
by the doorstep?</i>

20:04.291 --> 20:07.500
<i>It's a present I got you
to say sorry about last night.</i>

20:09.083 --> 20:10.875
Bollocks. Okay.

20:17.625 --> 20:19.000
Mmm!

20:25.166 --> 20:26.541
It's delicious. Thank you.

20:27.958 --> 20:30.583
No, um... it was only really enough for one.

20:32.125 --> 20:33.208
It was great.

20:34.708 --> 20:35.708
Really great.

20:38.416 --> 20:40.791
Uh, are you sure you won't have...

20:40.875 --> 20:42.000
No, I don't drink.

20:42.666 --> 20:43.708
Oh.

20:45.291 --> 20:46.833
Did you stop or...

20:47.666 --> 20:49.500
I just never really started.

20:50.083 --> 20:51.083
Mmm.

20:58.208 --> 21:00.166
So, do you like it?

21:01.583 --> 21:02.500
It's...

21:03.583 --> 21:05.458
it's unique, isn't it?

21:08.291 --> 21:09.791
I like its eyes.

21:13.958 --> 21:16.208
So, where are you from, originally?

21:16.791 --> 21:17.791
Um...

21:18.708 --> 21:20.958
Well, the north of England, and then, um...

21:21.541 --> 21:23.958
Catterick, Aldershot, then Belfast.

21:23.958 --> 21:25.708
- Everywhere and nowhere, really.
-

21:25.708 --> 21:29.125
My dad was in the military,
so we moved every two or three years.

21:29.125 --> 21:30.750
That must have been difficult.

21:31.875 --> 21:33.791
You sort of get used to it, I guess.

21:34.875 --> 21:37.416
And you weren't tempted
by the military life yourself?

21:37.500 --> 21:38.791
No, God no.

21:40.083 --> 21:41.458
No, at the end of the day,

21:41.458 --> 21:43.541
put on a uniform,
you gotta be prepared to...

21:44.666 --> 21:47.666
pull the trigger and end someone's life.

21:47.750 --> 21:50.541
- I just don't think I could do that.
- Really?

21:51.791 --> 21:53.166
- Yeah.
-

21:57.000 --> 21:59.208
So you sell cars instead?

22:00.083 --> 22:01.291
I sell luxury cars.

22:01.375 --> 22:04.416
- Right. There's a difference, is there?
- Oh, a huge difference.

22:05.375 --> 22:09.166
If someone wants a luxury car,
they're looking for an idea of themselves.

22:10.125 --> 22:12.458
- They're searching for a dream.
- Hmm.

22:13.750 --> 22:16.166
If you think about it,
it's actually quite moving.

22:19.875 --> 22:22.916
Well, I've met plenty
of barroom philosophers,

22:23.000 --> 22:25.625
but you're the first showroom philosopher.

22:29.333 --> 22:31.583
What about you? Do you like what you do?

22:31.583 --> 22:33.041
Mmm...

22:34.875 --> 22:36.500
Um... "Like..."

22:37.875 --> 22:39.541
is a pretty strong word.

22:40.875 --> 22:41.958
So why do you do it?

22:42.458 --> 22:44.416
Well, uh...

22:46.458 --> 22:47.458
I mean...

22:50.958 --> 22:53.583
it's... it's my job, you know?

23:02.375 --> 23:05.625
Well, thank you for dinner.
That was really... really lovely.

23:05.625 --> 23:07.208
Oh-- Yeah, yeah, well...

23:08.250 --> 23:10.541
- Uh...
- And sorry again about last night.

23:10.625 --> 23:12.875
No, it's-- it's fine, honestly.

23:12.875 --> 23:14.541
Uh... uh...

23:14.625 --> 23:15.833
Oh. Um...

23:16.541 --> 23:18.583
Uh, I hope your dad recovers quickly.

23:19.625 --> 23:20.958
Yeah. Thank you.

23:22.583 --> 23:23.916
-
- Um...

23:28.208 --> 23:30.375
Oh, yeah.

23:34.500 --> 23:35.708
Take care, Alice.

23:48.500 --> 23:50.125
What the fuck?

23:54.208 --> 23:57.000
The file on the latest
Jeremy Ascott litigation.

24:09.333 --> 24:10.250
Hello.

24:10.916 --> 24:12.541
<i>What are you doing now?</i>

24:12.625 --> 24:13.750
What, <i>now</i> now?

24:14.416 --> 24:15.833
I'm working.

24:15.833 --> 24:17.625
<i>I'd like to show you something.</i>

24:19.000 --> 24:21.083
- What? <i>- It's a surprise.</i>

24:22.375 --> 24:24.625
- Where are we going?
- Be patient.

24:24.625 --> 24:27.875
- Is this it?
- So full of questions. Trust me!

24:28.500 --> 24:31.166
- Two, please.
- All right. Ten pounds.

24:32.583 --> 24:33.583
- Thank you.
- What is this?

24:33.583 --> 24:35.083
- Thank you.
- Come on.

24:36.208 --> 24:37.208
Come on.

24:39.041 --> 24:40.166
- Uh--
- Oh.

24:40.666 --> 24:42.416
- Thank you.
- Pleasure.

24:52.416 --> 24:53.666
What is it?

24:54.250 --> 24:55.708
It's called <i>Longplayer.</i>

24:58.083 --> 24:59.708
These are Tibetan music bowls.

25:00.333 --> 25:03.125
They're playing a composition
that lasts for 1,000 years

25:03.125 --> 25:05.000
without ever repeating itself.

25:06.583 --> 25:08.375
It's controlled by a computer,

25:09.208 --> 25:11.375
and it never, ever stops.

25:12.833 --> 25:14.083
The plan is...

25:15.625 --> 25:18.791
to just let it keep playing
without stopping.

25:20.416 --> 25:22.750
Maybe, hopefully, for a thousand years.

25:25.500 --> 25:26.791
You are...

25:27.750 --> 25:30.375
so fucking random.

25:31.875 --> 25:33.041
Do you not like it?

