1:13:10.083 --> 1:13:11.291
What's that?

1:13:11.375 --> 1:13:13.208
They can't change.

1:13:13.208 --> 1:13:15.708
They do what they do again,
and again, and again,

1:13:15.708 --> 1:13:18.166
and they never, ever stop.

1:13:19.916 --> 1:13:23.666
The only thing you can do is try
to stay as far away from them as possible.

1:13:23.750 --> 1:13:26.541
The last thing you wanna do
is ever see him again.

1:13:26.625 --> 1:13:29.250
Try to find a way
to put things back together.

1:13:29.250 --> 1:13:33.583
- Loads of firms need people like you.
- No, that's all over now. I'm done.

1:13:42.041 --> 1:13:42.875
Phil.

1:13:44.041 --> 1:13:45.041
Alice.

1:13:49.625 --> 1:13:52.000
Would it surprise you
if I don't take your advice?

1:13:52.000 --> 1:13:54.125
Course it bloody wouldn't.

1:13:54.125 --> 1:13:55.500
But for God's sake,

1:13:56.500 --> 1:13:57.708
be careful.

1:13:57.708 --> 1:13:59.958
You're not gonna get better
than nine grand.

1:13:59.958 --> 1:14:01.666
You can-- Daniel will attest to it.

1:14:03.750 --> 1:14:04.875
- Right-oh.
- Mmm.

1:14:05.458 --> 1:14:06.500
Right-oh. So...

1:14:07.000 --> 1:14:08.500
- Wanna take a test drive?
- Yeah.

1:14:09.291 --> 1:14:11.416
- Hi.
- Hello.

1:14:13.333 --> 1:14:14.833
Any idea what you're looking for?

1:14:36.916 --> 1:14:38.833
- Ian Preston?
- Yes.

1:14:38.833 --> 1:14:41.000
Hi. I'm Alice Archer.

1:14:41.583 --> 1:14:43.916
I need to talk to you
about Robert Freegard.

1:14:47.416 --> 1:14:49.875
For two years,
we lived on the run from the IRA.

1:14:50.375 --> 1:14:53.500
We used fake names,
always moving from one place to the next.

1:14:54.458 --> 1:14:57.416
He told us the IRA wanted to kill us
to make an example of us.

1:14:57.916 --> 1:15:01.250
He said if we ever went home
to our families, we'd put them in danger.

1:15:01.250 --> 1:15:04.625
As time went on, he told us
we were candidates for a special program.

1:15:04.625 --> 1:15:05.833
A program?

1:15:05.833 --> 1:15:07.916
A recruitment program to join MI5.

1:15:08.625 --> 1:15:10.083
To make us officers like him.

1:15:10.083 --> 1:15:12.416
But to qualify,
we'd have to pass these tests.

1:15:12.500 --> 1:15:13.791
What kind of tests?

1:15:13.875 --> 1:15:15.125
Spy stuff.

1:15:15.916 --> 1:15:19.166
Delivering an envelope somewhere.
Following someone in the street.

1:15:19.250 --> 1:15:20.750
To prove you were good enough.

1:15:21.250 --> 1:15:23.375
And how long did all this go on for?

1:15:23.875 --> 1:15:24.916
For me, it was...

1:15:25.583 --> 1:15:26.583
four years.

1:15:28.333 --> 1:15:29.750
I know it sounds ridiculous,

1:15:29.750 --> 1:15:33.000
but he just has this way
of making you believe...

1:15:34.083 --> 1:15:35.166
you know, anything.

1:15:35.833 --> 1:15:37.833
It doesn't sound ridiculous to me.

1:15:45.083 --> 1:15:46.208
He told me something once.

1:15:47.416 --> 1:15:50.416
It was a... a throwaway thing,
but I never forgot it.

1:15:51.750 --> 1:15:54.625
He said everybody's got a story
that they wanna be told.

1:15:56.500 --> 1:15:58.000
What was your story?

1:15:59.708 --> 1:16:01.375
Well, look around you.

1:16:02.083 --> 1:16:03.250
I'm a farm boy.

1:16:03.916 --> 1:16:06.666
A simple life. Boring, mostly.

1:16:07.375 --> 1:16:09.083
He gave me the opposite of boring.

1:16:11.083 --> 1:16:12.875
What was the story you wanted to hear?

1:16:16.125 --> 1:16:17.666
That I could be free.

1:16:26.000 --> 1:16:27.375
Ian, can I ask you,

1:16:28.958 --> 1:16:30.458
how did you get away?

1:16:31.541 --> 1:16:33.041
Um...

1:16:36.625 --> 1:16:38.083
Well, I-- I didn't.

1:16:38.583 --> 1:16:39.750
Mmm...

1:16:39.750 --> 1:16:42.958
Yeah, one day, I woke up,
and-- and they were just gone.

1:16:45.916 --> 1:16:47.875
Yeah, I-- I didn't leave Freegard. Um...

1:16:48.958 --> 1:16:49.958
He left me.

1:16:51.250 --> 1:16:53.958
Him and Sophie and Mae
were-- were just gone.

1:16:54.500 --> 1:16:55.375
Mae?

1:16:55.875 --> 1:16:58.958
Yeah, Mae Hansen.
Yeah, she was with us for years.

1:16:59.916 --> 1:17:00.791
Hansen?

1:17:09.875 --> 1:17:11.875
Kidnapping?
He hasn't kidnapped anyone!

1:17:11.875 --> 1:17:15.875
In 1993, he takes three students
from Trent Hamilton University.

1:17:15.875 --> 1:17:18.208
Two of them, young women,
haven't been seen since.

1:17:18.208 --> 1:17:21.458
- They got in touch with their families.
- To ask for money.

1:17:21.458 --> 1:17:23.041
Sonny, for fuck's sake.

1:17:23.583 --> 1:17:24.625
Okay, look.

1:17:27.875 --> 1:17:32.083
All right. This is the legal definition
of kidnapping. Read it. Come on. Read it.

1:17:32.083 --> 1:17:34.833
I know what the legal definition is.
This is ridiculous.

1:17:34.833 --> 1:17:39.458
"Kidnapping is the taking of one person
or another by force or fraud."

1:17:39.458 --> 1:17:42.541
Fraud is what he's doing.
This is a common-law indictable offense.

1:17:42.625 --> 1:17:45.250
- We can make this stick.
- We? Are you a CPS lawyer now?

1:17:45.250 --> 1:17:47.041
No, but I'm more of a lawyer than you are.

1:17:49.875 --> 1:17:51.208
- I'm sorry.
-

1:17:51.208 --> 1:17:53.041
Sometimes I get a bit carried away.

1:17:53.625 --> 1:17:55.250
Yeah, you don't say, yeah.

1:18:03.125 --> 1:18:05.250
You say he's been using
Mae Hansen's name?

1:18:05.250 --> 1:18:07.625
Sometimes he uses Robert Hansen.

1:18:07.625 --> 1:18:11.208
Sometimes Robert Hansen-Freegard.
Sometimes just Robert Freegard.

1:18:15.416 --> 1:18:16.833
Well, why would he do that?

1:18:19.291 --> 1:18:20.458
Use her name in particular?

1:18:24.833 --> 1:18:27.250
Okay, I'm gonna run Mae Hansen
through the PNC.

1:18:28.375 --> 1:18:31.291
If she ever contacted emergency services,
there'll be an address.

1:18:31.375 --> 1:18:33.291
It's not much, but it's worth a try.

1:18:33.375 --> 1:18:37.125
But I'm warning you, the chances
of this going anywhere are...well...

1:18:38.583 --> 1:18:39.750
Thank you.

1:18:42.875 --> 1:18:44.500
Have you always lived here alone?

1:18:47.291 --> 1:18:48.291
Mmm--

1:18:48.791 --> 1:18:51.958
I still haven't been down the aisle,
if that's what you mean.

1:18:53.750 --> 1:18:54.750
You?

1:18:56.000 --> 1:18:58.125
Yes, unfortunately.

1:18:59.416 --> 1:19:00.250
Wasn't pretty.

1:19:16.041 --> 1:19:17.041
Sorry.

1:19:19.208 --> 1:19:21.208
What did you do in America?

1:19:22.000 --> 1:19:25.666
Um... I was an academic, in psychology.

1:19:28.875 --> 1:19:30.708
- Psychology?
- Yeah.

1:19:31.708 --> 1:19:33.583
So you better be careful.

1:19:34.541 --> 1:19:36.333
I can read you from a mile off.

1:19:36.333 --> 1:19:37.416
Oh, I will.

1:19:42.166 --> 1:19:43.916
So go on, then. Hmm?

1:19:45.375 --> 1:19:46.375
What's your secret?

1:19:48.250 --> 1:19:49.958
- My secret?
- Yeah.

1:19:51.083 --> 1:19:54.166
A guy like you. Lives all alone.

1:19:54.250 --> 1:19:56.166
Doesn't talk much about his past.

1:19:56.666 --> 1:19:59.791
Makes a mean spaghetti bolognese.

1:20:01.666 --> 1:20:03.208
What are you hiding?

1:20:06.833 --> 1:20:09.416
- Wow, you are good.
- I am!

1:20:11.250 --> 1:20:12.666
Phew. Uh...

1:20:12.750 --> 1:20:15.000
Well, Jenny...

1:20:15.625 --> 1:20:18.750
I had been meaning to--
to tell you something.

1:20:20.208 --> 1:20:21.916
Uh... it's about my job.

1:20:24.666 --> 1:20:26.291
I'm not really a car salesman.

1:21:00.208 --> 1:21:02.375
Mm. I love this place.

1:21:03.416 --> 1:21:04.708
Yeah, me too.

1:21:09.750 --> 1:21:12.833
Have you ever considered
doing something completely different?

1:21:13.541 --> 1:21:14.541
What do you mean?

1:21:15.916 --> 1:21:17.625
I mean, like a new career.

1:21:18.125 --> 1:21:20.708
Like what?

1:21:20.708 --> 1:21:24.458
Well, this is gonna sound
completely crazy...

1:21:24.458 --> 1:21:26.083
Go on.

1:21:28.666 --> 1:21:29.833
Uh...

1:21:32.291 --> 1:21:35.708
Well, there's a recruitment round
coming up.

1:21:36.625 --> 1:21:37.625
At work.

1:21:38.708 --> 1:21:40.208
For intelligence analysts.

1:21:40.208 --> 1:21:42.000
What?

1:21:43.166 --> 1:21:44.791
Oh my God.

1:21:44.875 --> 1:21:47.416
What? You think I should become a spy?

1:21:47.500 --> 1:21:50.375
No, you wouldn't be a field officer,
you'd be an analyst.

1:21:52.625 --> 1:21:54.833
You have a background in psychology.

1:21:55.791 --> 1:21:57.958
You can read people,
work out their motivations.

1:21:57.958 --> 1:22:01.041
I-- I think you'd be really,
really good at it.

1:22:01.541 --> 1:22:04.791
- But I'm American.
- We recruit NATO allies all the time.

1:22:06.666 --> 1:22:08.041
-

1:22:09.375 --> 1:22:12.500
Robert,
I gotta tell you something.

1:22:13.958 --> 1:22:16.000
Oh, God. Um, okay, here goes.

1:22:16.000 --> 1:22:18.500
Um... I am actually on a...

1:22:19.541 --> 1:22:22.208
pretty intense cocktail
of antidepressants.

1:22:22.958 --> 1:22:24.125
Since my divorce.

1:22:25.625 --> 1:22:27.333
So...

1:22:29.166 --> 1:22:32.750
So? I don't see why
that would be a problem.

1:22:42.625 --> 1:22:44.833
- And a mushy pea?
- Gross.

1:22:44.833 --> 1:22:46.500
- Really?
- Yeah!

1:22:49.250 --> 1:22:50.625
Listen, Jenny, uh...

1:22:50.625 --> 1:22:52.583
- If you are gonna take this job...
- Mmm?

1:22:52.583 --> 1:22:55.500
There are a couple of things
we need to discuss.

1:22:59.541 --> 1:23:01.750
You mentioned you had
a lot of student debt?

1:23:02.250 --> 1:23:03.750
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1:23:04.875 --> 1:23:07.000
It might turn out
to be a bit of a problem.

1:23:07.500 --> 1:23:09.000
- Really?
- Yeah.

1:23:09.000 --> 1:23:12.208
Everyone who goes to college
in the States is in debt.

1:23:13.125 --> 1:23:14.000
Yeah, I know.

1:23:14.000 --> 1:23:18.833
In this country, uh, the security services
see large debts owed by members of staff

1:23:18.833 --> 1:23:21.083
as a potential liability.

1:23:22.000 --> 1:23:23.750
- Yeah, like a blackmail risk.
-

1:23:23.750 --> 1:23:26.083
- Really? Are you kidding me?
- No.

1:23:26.708 --> 1:23:28.416
-
- I know. It's ridiculous.

1:23:28.500 --> 1:23:31.166
They're just--
they're just so set in their ways.

1:23:31.250 --> 1:23:33.083
It's-- it's absurd.

1:23:34.916 --> 1:23:36.625
How much is it, your student debt?

1:23:37.166 --> 1:23:40.375
Shit, I mean,
last time I checked, about...

1:23:41.125 --> 1:23:42.458
$80,000.

1:23:43.875 --> 1:23:46.083
- Yeah. Wow.
- Yeah, that's America.

1:23:46.875 --> 1:23:47.875
Um...

1:23:49.083 --> 1:23:51.666
And you have, uh...
you have no way of paying it back?

1:23:52.166 --> 1:23:54.291
I mean, let me check my pockets.

1:23:54.375 --> 1:23:55.708
No.

1:23:58.875 --> 1:23:59.875
Shit.

1:24:00.791 --> 1:24:01.958
Um...

1:24:01.958 --> 1:24:04.375
Well, listen,
if it really is a problem, I...

1:24:05.375 --> 1:24:07.208
I guess I could ask my folks.

1:24:07.208 --> 1:24:08.250
I mean...

1:24:08.833 --> 1:24:10.208
maybe I could ask them.

1:24:13.166 --> 1:24:15.166
Do you really think
this could be her?

1:24:15.750 --> 1:24:17.291
Date of birth matches.

1:24:19.458 --> 1:24:22.083
-

1:24:23.125 --> 1:24:25.291
You just let me
take the lead, okay?

1:24:29.583 --> 1:24:30.708
Mae Hansen?

1:24:33.166 --> 1:24:34.000
Yes.

1:24:34.000 --> 1:24:39.000
Did you attend Trent Hamilton University
with Ian Preston and Sophie Jones?

1:24:41.541 --> 1:24:43.500
- Yes.
- I'm Detective Constable Chandra.

1:24:43.500 --> 1:24:45.125
We're here about Robert Freegard.

1:24:45.125 --> 1:24:47.958
- Or Hansen-Freegard, as he's also known.
- He's not here at the moment.

1:24:49.833 --> 1:24:50.833
May we come in?

1:24:55.500 --> 1:24:57.708
<i>Oh, Jim!
Oh, the chickens are coming in the boat!</i>

1:24:57.708 --> 1:24:58.916
Thank you.

1:25:02.625 --> 1:25:04.875
<i>Depends. I'm going to the forest.</i>

1:25:05.500 --> 1:25:06.541
<i>Please, Jim!</i>

1:25:06.625 --> 1:25:07.875
Who are these children?

1:25:08.375 --> 1:25:09.583
They're our girls.

1:25:10.458 --> 1:25:11.541
Mine and Rob's.

1:25:18.541 --> 1:25:20.166
How often do you see him?

1:25:22.791 --> 1:25:24.125
He comes and goes.

1:25:25.250 --> 1:25:26.708
His work is very important.

1:25:28.583 --> 1:25:30.291
But he looks after you?

1:25:31.750 --> 1:25:32.958
You and the children?

1:25:39.375 --> 1:25:40.375
Look, Mae.

1:25:41.416 --> 1:25:42.458
Are you okay?

1:25:44.666 --> 1:25:45.750
Can we help you?

1:25:47.708 --> 1:25:49.541
If you ask for help, I can help you.

1:25:55.916 --> 1:25:57.458
He said this would happen.

1:25:58.208 --> 1:25:59.250
What?

1:25:59.250 --> 1:26:03.541
He said you would come
and try to test me to see if I was loyal.

1:26:05.125 --> 1:26:06.208
No, Mae.

1:26:06.791 --> 1:26:08.041
This isn't a test.

1:26:08.125 --> 1:26:10.958
- Unless you've something else to say, go.
- He's in danger.

1:26:12.416 --> 1:26:13.250
What?

1:26:13.750 --> 1:26:17.375
Rob may be in danger
because of the important work he does,

1:26:17.375 --> 1:26:20.458
and we need to find him
because we need to warn him.

1:26:21.041 --> 1:26:22.333
That's all I can say.

1:26:23.083 --> 1:26:25.666
You understand? It's national security.

1:26:27.208 --> 1:26:31.166
Now, do you know of anything
that can help us find him?

1:26:31.958 --> 1:26:34.333
- An address, a-- a phone number, anything.
- Listen.

1:26:34.333 --> 1:26:36.625
- I think we should--
- Mae, we need to find him.

1:26:36.625 --> 1:26:38.125
We need to warn him.

1:26:38.625 --> 1:26:39.625
Please.

1:26:46.708 --> 1:26:47.833
There's a notebook.

1:26:49.041 --> 1:26:51.541
In his sock drawer.
It has phone numbers in it.

1:26:54.333 --> 1:26:56.250
I can't believe it you did that.
I could be fired.

1:26:56.250 --> 1:26:59.041
It's just mobile phone numbers.
Line after line of them.

1:26:59.125 --> 1:27:00.916
- Must be hundreds.
- It doesn't prove anything.

1:27:01.000 --> 1:27:03.291
Doesn't prove anything? Are you serious?

1:27:03.375 --> 1:27:05.250
- This could be how we track him down!
- Then what?

1:27:05.250 --> 1:27:06.916
- Come on!
- I'm serious. Where's the crime?

1:27:07.000 --> 1:27:08.333
Go on, you're the lawyer. Where?

1:27:08.333 --> 1:27:12.208
And even if we did get all this to court,
what will a jury make of Mae Hansen?

1:27:12.208 --> 1:27:14.875
- She's the mother of his children!
- Don't you see?

1:27:14.875 --> 1:27:16.833
He never ever stops.

1:27:16.833 --> 1:27:19.875
He goes on and on,
destroying people's lives,

1:27:19.875 --> 1:27:21.500
until somebody stops him.

1:27:30.208 --> 1:27:33.708
Look, I'm sorry, all right?
That must have been...

1:27:34.583 --> 1:27:37.333
That must have been hard,
seeing the kids and that...

1:27:39.666 --> 1:27:40.833
It's not enough.

1:27:42.333 --> 1:27:43.708
None of this is enough.

1:27:55.041 --> 1:27:57.750
Mum! You don't listen!

1:28:39.125 --> 1:28:41.875
<i>The number you have dialed
has not been recognized.</i>

1:28:41.875 --> 1:28:43.041
<i>Please check and--</i>

1:29:38.458 --> 1:29:40.791
It is a bit strange
they still haven't called.

1:29:40.875 --> 1:29:42.958
It's a lot of money, Robert.

1:29:43.541 --> 1:29:44.541
Takes time.

1:29:48.083 --> 1:29:50.916
Look, I don't have to apply for this job
this time round.

1:29:51.416 --> 1:29:52.416
I can wait.

1:29:53.291 --> 1:29:54.750
I mean, to be honest...

1:29:55.666 --> 1:29:57.583
I'm not even really sure I should apply.

1:29:57.583 --> 1:30:00.333
I don't think you realize
that there won't be a next time.

1:30:02.041 --> 1:30:02.916
Oh...

1:30:05.750 --> 1:30:07.666
- Robert, what are you doing?
-

1:30:10.458 --> 1:30:11.583
What are you doing?

1:30:13.416 --> 1:30:15.041
What the fuck are you doing?

1:30:15.125 --> 1:30:18.041
- You don't need those things.
- Those are my meds! I need my meds!

1:30:18.125 --> 1:30:20.625
No, we're gonna get you off them,
starting today.

1:30:20.625 --> 1:30:22.875
Those aren't drugs
you can quit, cold turkey.

1:30:22.875 --> 1:30:25.041
- I can't do that.
- Yes, you can. You can.

1:30:25.125 --> 1:30:27.250
Yes, you can. I'm right here, okay?

1:30:27.833 --> 1:30:30.500
I'm right here. I'm not gonna let
anything bad happen to you.

1:30:30.500 --> 1:30:32.208
I promise you, Jenny.

1:30:33.083 --> 1:30:34.833
This is a good thing, okay?

1:30:35.625 --> 1:30:37.541
It's a good thing. It's a good thing.

1:30:38.916 --> 1:30:39.833
Hey.

1:31:01.083 --> 1:31:03.125
- Out all night again?
- Piss off.

1:31:05.541 --> 1:31:07.708
- You were right.
- What?

1:31:08.375 --> 1:31:09.583
He never stops.

1:31:10.875 --> 1:31:11.875
Can you come with me?

1:31:11.875 --> 1:31:13.250
Where are we going?

1:31:13.750 --> 1:31:15.125
To the American embassy.

1:31:18.166 --> 1:31:19.291
Give me ten minutes.

1:31:22.208 --> 1:31:23.041
Five.

1:31:24.375 --> 1:31:27.791
Thank you for coming, Miss Archer.
Special Agent Harland.

1:31:28.500 --> 1:31:30.000
Please, follow me.

1:31:34.666 --> 1:31:35.916
Have a seat.

1:31:41.500 --> 1:31:42.500
So,

1:31:43.125 --> 1:31:46.666
I understand that you have
some experience of this guy.

1:31:47.291 --> 1:31:48.666
What's all this about?

1:31:50.375 --> 1:31:55.083
The FBI is concerned about the whereabouts
of an American citizen.

1:31:56.291 --> 1:31:57.333
Jenny Jackson.

1:31:57.833 --> 1:32:01.458
She's been here in the UK
for three months.

1:32:02.000 --> 1:32:05.166
Usually, she calls her parents
several times a week,

1:32:05.250 --> 1:32:06.500
but about three weeks ago,

1:32:06.500 --> 1:32:08.833
she darn near fell off
the face of the Earth.

1:32:09.625 --> 1:32:11.291
Then a couple of days ago,

